Capacity of a Queue

Source: R/Queue.R
capacity.Rd

capacity returns the maximum number of elements that a Queue object can contain.

capacity(x)

Arguments

x

A Queue object.

Value

A numeric value.

See also

Queue, queue

Author

Simon Garnier, garnier@njit.edu

Examples

balloon <- video(system.file("sample_vid/Balloon.mp4", package = "Rvision"))
buf <- queue(balloon)
capacity(buf)
#> [1] 10
